The paper discusses the development of a search tool based on interestingness, which is a concept commonly used in information retrieval (IR) research. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The tool also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which falls under cs.CL. The use of machine learning algorithms for interestingness functions suggests cs.DL as another possible sub-category. The tool also involves database management, which falls under cs.DB. Finally, the tool's flexibility and ability to work with different interestingness functions suggests cs.AI as a possible sub-category.
